    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>test.split(\"\\\\|\",999);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Specifing a <strong>limit</strong> or max will be <strong>accurate</strong> for examples like: \"boo|||a\" or \"||boo|\" or \" |||\"</p>\n\n<p>But  <code>test.split(\"\\\\|\");</code> will return different length strings arrays for the same examples.</p>\n\n<p>use reference: <a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/split-string-java-examples/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">link</a></p>\n"
